  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Cded in remission patients with high calprotectin&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Due to the success of diet in achieving remission in mild-moderate forms of the disease, and&#xD;
      an increasing number of patients with loss of response to available drugs despite increasing&#xD;
      dose and pathophysiology of the disease, the aim of the present study is to evaluate whether&#xD;
      there is response with the addition of diet therapy in patients with moderate/severe forms of&#xD;
      CD receiving biologic therapy (infliximab or adalimumab) and presenting active disease.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
